# What is make?
#
# - make is a scripting tool that is used for building executable  according to commands.
#
# - make tool parse an input file "makefile" to define rules that it will run.
#
# - two types of make (GNU - Borland).
#####################################################
#
# - Why we need make?
#
# -> to organize the compilation process
# -> to run our tools and scripts
# -> to automate the process
# -> to full control on the outputs and its time.

#### Summery >> needs of make >> to organize and automate outputs of the copilation process according to commands.

